Head: with ca. 16 ocelli (
Fig. 50
), arranged in 4 rows (1: 3: 5: 7).

Distribution and habitat: This species is only known from three sites in the Porongurup Range National Park, situated approximately 34 km north of Albany ( Fig. 6 ). The dominant vegetation in this area includes tall karri (
Eucalyptus diversicolor
) forests and mixed karri, jarrah (
E. marginata
) and marri (
Corymbia calophylla
) forests. Specimens were collected by hand from under rotting logs. This species occurs with
A. julianneae
, although the level of sympatry is not currently known.
